igned to improve the status of women throughout the twentieth century. The book provides a radical re-assessment of this period of women’s history and in doing so makes a significant contribution to ongoing debates about the shape and impact of the women’s movement in twentieth-century Britain.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aWomenxPolitical activityzGreat BritainxHistory. 0aWomen's rightszGreat BritainxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aCitizenship.  aconservative.  adomesticity.  afemale agency.  afeminism.  ahousewives.  avoluntary women’s organisations.  awomen’s liberation movement.  awomen’s movement.  awomen’s rights.1 aBeaumont, Caitríona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978178499194440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784991944423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784991944/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles